# Spec: Collapsible Sidebar — RiskShield

> Derived from: `docs/side_bar_refactor/0. Pre Spec/Pre Spec`
> Status: Ready for review
> Scope: Single component refactor + minimal CSS variable additions

---

## Objective

Redesign `Sidebar.tsx` into a **floating island** with a **frosted-glass surface**, a
smooth expand/collapse toggle, and icon-only collapsed state with hover tooltips.

This is the **launch UI change** that establishes the visual direction for the app's
eventual modernisation pass. The implementation must be:

- Contained to one component (`Sidebar.tsx`) and one CSS file (`index.css`).
- Zero new npm dependencies (no Framer Motion, no headless UI).
- Backward-compatible with the existing theming system (CSS custom properties, light/dark,
  custom accent colour, branding config).
- Readable by a future agent or developer unfamiliar with this session.

### User stories

- As a PMO user I want the sidebar to collapse to a slim icon rail so I have more
  horizontal space for large registers and dashboards.
- As a PMO user I want the sidebar to feel visually distinct and premium so the app
  reads as a polished product, not a template.
- As a PMO user my collapsed/expanded preference is remembered across reloads.
- As a user with `prefers-reduced-motion` I get instant state transitions instead of
  animated ones.
- As a keyboard/screen-reader user I can expand and collapse the sidebar without a
  pointer, and collapsed nav items expose their labels for assistive technologies.

