## Visual Design

### Floating Island

The sidebar is a vertically floating panel that is visually detached from the viewport
edges. It is **not** position-fixed — it remains a flex item in the shell so the main
content area reflows naturally.

```
Shell layout (simplified):
┌─────────────────────────────────┐  100vh
│  [sidebar column]  [main area]  │
│   width: 252px       flex: 1    │
└─────────────────────────────────┘

Sidebar column (expanded): 252px wide
  └─ Island (inner div): margin 10px all sides
       → visible width: 232px
       → height: calc(100vh - 20px)
       → border-radius: 16px

Sidebar column (collapsed): 68px wide
  └─ Island: margin 10px all sides
       → visible width: 48px
```

The outer sidebar `<div>` holds the column width and provides the margin space. The inner
island `<div>` is the visible frosted panel.

### Frosted Glass Surface

The island uses `backdrop-filter: blur(18px) saturate(160%)` on a semi-transparent
background. Because the app content scrolls beneath it, the blur composites live
page content — giving the genuine "glass" effect rather than a static texture.

**Light mode** (default, sidebar `--sidebar` = `#1b1e2b`):
```
background: rgba(15, 17, 25, 0.82)
backdrop-filter: blur(18px) saturate(160%)
border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.07)
box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.28), 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18)
```

**Dark mode** (sidebar `--sidebar` = `#121317`):
```
background: rgba(8, 9, 14, 0.88)
backdrop-filter: blur(18px) saturate(160%)
border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05)
box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.48), 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.32)
```

These values are exposed as four new CSS custom properties added to `index.css` so they
participate in the existing theme system:

```css
/* index.css — added to :root[data-theme="light"] block */
--sidebar-glass-bg:      rgba(15, 17, 25, 0.82);
--sidebar-glass-border:  rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.07);
--sidebar-glass-shadow:  0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.28),
                         0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18);

/* Added to :root[data-theme="dark"] block */
--sidebar-glass-bg:      rgba(8, 9, 14, 0.88);
--sidebar-glass-border:  rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
--sidebar-glass-shadow:  0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.48),
                         0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.32);
```

`backdrop-filter` is applied inline; it does not vary by theme so no CSS variable is
needed for it.

**Fallback**: Browsers without `backdrop-filter` support receive the full opaque
`--sidebar` colour. The glass is progressive enhancement — the layout is identical.

### Accent Glow (subtle)

The active nav item retains the brand-colour highlight. The toggle button gains a very
subtle inner glow using `box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px var(--brand)` on focus — no colour
variables need changing.

