## Animation Specification

All transitions are applied as **inline style `transition` properties** on the
individual elements, not via a CSS class swap. This keeps them within the existing
inline-style pattern and avoids specificity conflicts.

### Width transition (column)

```ts
// Outer column div
transition: "width 300ms cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)"
// Easing: slightly spring-like — decelerates rapidly then settles.
// 300ms is perceptibly snappy but not rushed.
```

### Label opacity + translate (nav item labels)

Labels slide out to the left and fade when collapsing; reverse on expand.

```ts
// The label <span> inside each nav item
style={{
  opacity:    isCollapsed ? 0 : 1,
  width:      isCollapsed ? 0 : "auto",
  maxWidth:   isCollapsed ? 0 : 160,
  overflow:   "hidden",
  whiteSpace: "nowrap",
  transform:  isCollapsed ? "translateX(-8px)" : "translateX(0)",
  transition: isCollapsed
    ? "opacity 120ms ease, transform 120ms ease, max-width 200ms ease"
    : "opacity 160ms ease 80ms, transform 160ms ease 80ms, max-width 300ms cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)",
}}
```

The expand path has an 80ms delay on opacity/transform so the width opens first then the
text fades in — avoids the "text clips into existence" artefact.

### Section header labels

Same pattern as nav item labels — fade + translate, with the same timing.

### Elements hidden in collapsed state

These elements receive `opacity: 0; pointer-events: none; max-height: 0; overflow: hidden`
when collapsed, transitioning back on expand:

| Element | Collapsed | Transition |
|---|---|---|
| Global search bar | Hidden | `opacity 150ms ease, max-height 200ms ease` |
| Portfolio stats block | Hidden | `opacity 150ms ease, max-height 250ms ease` |
| Keyboard shortcuts hints | Hidden | `opacity 100ms ease` |
| User name + role text | Hidden | `opacity 120ms ease` |
| Section header text labels | Hidden (see above) | `opacity 120ms ease` |

The icons and avatar image always remain visible.

### Reduced motion

A `<style>` tag inside `Sidebar.tsx` (like the existing `rs-kbd-hints` style) adds:

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .rs-sidebar-island,
  .rs-sidebar-island * {
    transition-duration: 0ms !important;
    animation-duration: 0ms !important;
  }
}
```

The island `<div>` is given `className="rs-sidebar-island"`.

