## Collapsed State — Content Rules

When `isCollapsed === true`:

| Content | Behaviour |
|---|---|
| `BrandMark` icon | Visible, centred |
| App name + strapline | Invisible (opacity 0, max-width 0) |
| Dark-mode toggle button | Visible (icon only), repositioned below logo |
| Collapse toggle chevron | Visible, remains top-right of island |
| Nav section labels ("Risk", "Change", etc.) | Invisible |
| Nav item icons | Visible, centred in the 48px island |
| Nav item labels | Invisible (see animation spec) |
| Global search | Invisible + `aria-hidden="true"`, `tabIndex={-1}` on input |
| Portfolio stats | Invisible |
| Keyboard hints block | Invisible |
| User name + role | Invisible |
| User avatar (initials circle) | Visible, centred |
| Sign-out button icon | Visible |

### Nav items in collapsed state — alignment

In collapsed state, each nav item div:
```ts
justifyContent: "center",
padding: "8px 0",
```

The icon is centred in the 48px island. The label span is present in the DOM but
visually hidden (for accessibility — screen readers still read the nav).

