## Tooltip Behaviour (Collapsed State)

When collapsed and pointer-fine devices, hovering a nav item shows a floating label
to the **right** of the sidebar island.

### Implementation

A `<style>` tag inside `Sidebar.tsx` handles this via CSS. Each nav item wrapper gets
the class `rs-nav-item`, and a sibling `<span>` element holds the tooltip text:

```tsx
<div className="rs-nav-item" style={{ position: "relative", ... }}>
  <icon />
  {isCollapsed && (
    <span className="rs-nav-tooltip" aria-hidden="true">
      {item.label}
    </span>
  )}
</div>
```

The CSS (in the `<style>` tag):

```css
@media (pointer: fine) {
  .rs-nav-item .rs-nav-tooltip {
    position: absolute;
    left: calc(100% + 10px);
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%) translateX(-6px);
    background: var(--surface);
    color: var(--text);
    border: 1px solid var(--stroke);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 5px 10px;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    font-weight: 600;
    white-space: nowrap;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-8);
    opacity: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    transition: opacity 120ms ease, transform 120ms ease;
    z-index: 60;
  }

  .rs-nav-item:hover .rs-nav-tooltip {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(-50%) translateX(0);
  }
}
```

The tooltip:
- Uses `var(--surface)`, `var(--text)`, `var(--stroke)`, `var(--shadow-8)` — these resolve
  correctly in both light and dark schemes automatically.
- Is `aria-hidden="true"` — screen readers get the label from the visible (but
  visually-hidden) nav item text span.
- Only renders when `isCollapsed === true` (React conditional), so no orphaned tooltips
  in expanded state.
- Only shows on `pointer: fine` (no touch), matching the existing keyboard hints pattern.

