## Code Style

Follow existing patterns exactly. The key additions:

```tsx
// ✅ Correct — inline transition with ternary for collapsed state
<div
  style={{
    width: isCollapsed ? 68 : 252,
    flexShrink: 0,
    transition: "width 300ms cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)",
  }}
>
  {/* Island */}
  <div
    className="rs-sidebar-island"
    style={{
      background: "var(--sidebar-glass-bg)",
      backdropFilter: "blur(18px) saturate(160%)",
      WebkitBackdropFilter: "blur(18px) saturate(160%)", // Safari
      border: "1px solid var(--sidebar-glass-border)",
      boxShadow: "var(--sidebar-glass-shadow)",
      borderRadius: 16,
      margin: 10,
      height: "calc(100vh - 20px)",
      display: "flex",
      flexDirection: "column",
      overflow: "hidden",
    }}
  >
    {/* content */}
  </div>
</div>

// ✅ Correct — collapsed label hide pattern
<span
  style={{
    opacity: isCollapsed ? 0 : 1,
    maxWidth: isCollapsed ? 0 : 160,
    overflow: "hidden",
    whiteSpace: "nowrap",
    transition: isCollapsed
      ? "opacity 120ms ease, max-width 200ms ease"
      : "opacity 160ms ease 80ms, max-width 300ms cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)",
  }}
>
  {item.label}
</span>

// ❌ Wrong — do not add a new CSS module or use className for anything other
//    than the reduced-motion hook and tooltip CSS
// ❌ Wrong — do not add Framer Motion, react-spring, or any animation library
// ❌ Wrong — do not use position: fixed for the sidebar
```

**Naming**:
- State: `isCollapsed` (boolean)
- Toggle handler: `handleToggleSidebar`
- localStorage key constant: `SIDEBAR_COLLAPSED_KEY`
- CSS class on island: `rs-sidebar-island` (matches existing `rs-*` prefix)
- CSS class on nav items: `rs-nav-item`
- CSS class on tooltip: `rs-nav-tooltip`

