## Boundaries

**Always:**
- `npm run typecheck` passes before considering any task done.
- Follow inline-style + CSS-var pattern — no exceptions.
- Keep `WebkitBackdropFilter` alongside `backdropFilter` for Safari support.
- The island must not clip nav items vertically — `overflowY: "auto"` on the nav
  scroll region.

**Ask first:**
- Any change to the sidebar's position in the flex layout (e.g. making it `position: fixed`).
- Adding any npm dependency, including animation libraries.
- Exposing `isCollapsed` state outside `Sidebar.tsx` (e.g. via context) — this spec
  intentionally keeps it local.
- Changing the `Shell` layout in `App.tsx` beyond what the width transition requires.

**Never:**
- Hardcode colours outside the CSS variable system.
- Use `var()` with an alpha suffix hack (`${T.brand}33`) — use `color-mix()` or
  the `alpha()` helper from `tokens.ts`.
- Use `!important` anywhere except the reduced-motion override.
- Remove the keyboard shortcuts block from the DOM — it must stay (just hidden when
  collapsed) so the feature is not lost.

